
1. The "Hostess" Screen (Managing Tables)
Imagine a digital map of your restaurant. This screen helps the person at the front door seat customers.
•	How it works: Each table on the screen is a button.
•	Colors: If a table is Green, it's empty. If it's Red, people are eating there. Blue would mean it is a reserved table.
•	Action: When a customer arrives, the hostess taps a table to "check them in."
•	Database link: This screen talks to your Mesa (Table) and Reserva (Reservation) lists.
2. The "Server" Screen (Taking Orders)
This is what the waiters use. It looks like a fast-food menu with big buttons.
•	How it works: The waiter taps "Hamburger" or "Soda."
•	Safety: If someone is allergic to gluten, the waiter can hit a "Gluten-Free" button, and the app will hide everything they can't eat.
•	The Ticket: As they tap, the app adds up the price automatically so the waiter doesn't have to do math.
•	Database link: This screen uses your Menu and Orden (Order) lists.
3. The "Manager" Screen (Watching the Food)
This is for the boss to see if the restaurant is running out of food.
•	The Magic Part: Every time a waiter sells a hamburger, the app "whispers" to the inventory: "Hey, we just used one bun and one beef patty, please subtract them from the shelf."
•	Alerts: If you only have 2 tomatoes left, the screen will flash Yellow to tell the boss to buy more.
•	Database link: This screen uses your Inventario (Inventory) and Receta (Recipe) lists.

