Detailed View: The Hostess Screen (Floor Management)
 
What it looks like:
A big digital map that looks exactly like your restaurant's physical layout. Each table is a large, easy-to-tap button.
The Color Coding (The "Traffic Light" System):
•	🟢 Green (Disponible): These tables are empty. The hostess can seat someone here immediately.
•	🔴 Red (Ocupada): People are currently sitting here and eating. The hostess knows not to send anyone to these tables.
•	🔵 Blue (Reservada): This is our new addition! This table is blocked because someone called ahead. Even if it looks empty, the hostess knows it’s saved for later.
How it works (Step-by-Step):
1.	Greeting: A customer walks in.
2.	Checking the Map: The hostess looks at the screen for a Green table.
3.	The "Check-In": The hostess taps the Green table button.
o	A small window pops up asking: "Start new order for Table 5?" * They hit "Yes."
4.	The Update: The table instantly turns Red on everyone’s screen (including the waiters' screens) so they know it’s now busy.
The "Smart" Connection (Behind the Scenes):
•	Reservation Sync: Every morning, the app checks the Reserva list in your database. If there is a booking for 2:00 PM, at 1:30 PM that table automatically turns Blue so nobody else sits there by mistake.
•	Automatic Cleaning: When a waiter finishes a payment on the Server Screen, the table on the Hostess Screen turns Green again automatically.
The "Waitlist" Timer
If all the tables are Red or Blue, we could add a little clock icon in the corner.
•	It shows the hostess how long people have been sitting at each table (e.g., "Table 4 has been eating for 45 minutes").
•	This helps the hostess tell a waiting customer: "It will be about a 10-minute wait!"

