Detailed View: The Server Screen (Taking Orders)
 
What it looks like: Imagine a screen divided into two halves. On the right, there are big, colorful buttons for food categories. On the left, there is a digital "receipt" that lists everything the customer is ordering.
The Main Features:
•	Big Buttons (Quick Tap): Instead of typing "Hamburger," the waiter just taps a big icon that says "Burgers." This opens a sub-menu with your specific items from the Menu table, like "Classic Burger" or "Veggie Burger."
•	Smart Safety Filters: This is a key part of your database.
o	Gluten-Free / Vegan Buttons: At the top of the screen, there are "Safety Toggles."
o	If the waiter taps "Gluten-Free," the screen instantly hides every item that contains gluten.
o	This helps the waiter tell the customer, "Here is exactly what you can safely eat!"
•	The "Spicy" Meter: For items like tacos or wings, a small pop-up appears asking for the nivel_picante (Spicy Level: 1 to 5). The waiter taps the number the customer wants.
How it works (Step-by-Step):
1.	Selecting the Table: The waiter taps a Red table on their screen to open the bill.
2.	Adding Items: They tap "Soda" and then "Cheeseburger."
o	The app instantly pulls the price from your database and adds it to the total.
3.	Sending to Kitchen: The waiter hits a big green "SEND" button.
o	This creates the Orden (Order) in your database and tells the kitchen what to cook.
4.	The Live Receipt: The customer can see their total growing in real-time, so there are no surprises when the bill arrives.
The "Smart" Connection (Behind the Scenes):
•	Inventory Check: If the kitchen runs out of "Fish Tacos," the button on this screen automatically turns Grey and becomes un-clickable. This prevents the waiter from selling something the restaurant doesn't have.
•	Employee Tracking: Because the waiter had to "Log In," the app knows exactly which Empleado (Employee) took the order.
The "Split Bill" Button
Sometimes a big group wants to pay separately. We can add a button that automatically takes the Detalle_Orden (the list of food) and divides the total by the number of people at the table.

