Detailed View: The Manager Screen (Inventory & Money)
What it looks like: A dashboard with progress bars and lists. Instead of colorful food buttons, it has charts that show what is happening in the kitchen and the bank account.
The Main Features:
•	The "Magic" Inventory Countdown: * This is the part we talked about earlier. Because your database has a Receta (Recipe) table, the manager doesn't have to count steaks or buns.
o	The app does it automatically! Every time a "Server" screen finishes a sale, this screen updates the numbers in real-time.
•	Low Stock "Traffic Lights":
o	🔴 Red: Out of stock! (e.g., 0 tomatoes). The app puts this at the top of the list.
o	🟡 Yellow: Running low. (e.g., Only 5 sodas left). This is your early warning.
o	🟢 Green: Plenty of stock.
•	Supplier Quick-Call: Next to every low-stock item, there is a button to contact the Proveedor (Supplier). One tap sends an email or order to get more food delivered.
•	Money Tracker: A simple graph showing how much money was made today using the Pago table.
How it works (Step-by-Step):
1.	Morning Check: The manager opens the app and looks at the Yellow alerts. They see they are low on "Carne de res" (Beef).
2.	The Sale: Throughout the day, as waiters sell burgers, the manager sees the beef bar slowly move down.
3.	End of Day: The manager clicks on the "Reports" button. The app pulls data from Empleado and Orden to show who the best waiter was today.
4.	Payroll: The manager uses the Pago_Empleado section to see who needs to be paid this week based on their hours worked.
The "Smart" Connection (Behind the Scenes):
•	Auto-Order: If you want to be really fancy, the app can be set to "Auto-Order." When the milk hits 2 cartons, it automatically sends a message to the dairy supplier!
•	Waste Tracking: If a cook drops a plate, the manager can hit a "Waste" button to manually subtract 1 item from the inventory so the numbers stay perfect.
